<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-235-122 </DOCNO><DOCID>09 826 795</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  Jan 31 1991 n1602* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (England) 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Cincom answers IBM's AD/Cycle with AD/Advantage system. (programdevelopment system) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Cincom Systems Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   AD/Advantage (CASE software) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Program Development ToolsProduct IntroductionSoftware PackagesComputer-Aided Software Engineering.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>CINCOM ANSWERS IBM'S AD/CYCLE WITH AD/ADVANTAGE SYSTEMandM;Cincom Systems Inc has been beavering away for six years to develop its fulllife-cycle technology that offers benefits associated with object-orientedtechnology, such as re-usable logic components, via traditional proceduralprogramming techniques.andP;  Yesterday the product, called AD/Advantage, waslaunched worldwide from the UK.andP;  It is described as an applicationdevelopment environment that automates the whole application life cycle.andP;  Theproduct has a generator that generates pieces of logic or code, or it cantake icon-driven logic components out of upper CASE tools such as IEW andExcelerator and generate code into AD/Advantage from them.andP;  It can alsointegrate code from an expert system with the rest of an application viaXpertRule, itself a workstation-based expert system from Attar Software.andP;  Asfor database design, AD/Advantage can currently take information from DB2 andSupra catalogues and then generates SQL fragments to run throughapplications.andP;  The various application components are generated into thedevelopment environment and run in prototype.andP;  Only after this has beensuccessfully completed is there any need to generate code, which is generatedin components and is maintained in a library of re-usable modules.andO;Consequently, if a component is modified it will automatically recompose allthe affected programs.andP;  AD/Advantage generates code in Cincom's Mantis fourthgeneration language or in standard Cobol.andP;  However, while it can accessprograms written in Cobol, Fortran and other languages, AD/Advantage can onlyre-use code that has been generated within its development environment, withthe exception of existing Mantis applications, which can be re-engineered.andO;Cincom denied that this was a system likely to be taken up only by Mantisusers, pointing to the fact that TSB Plc and Norwich Union have alreadybought into it and their applications are mainly in Cobol.andP;  But the fullbenefit of AD/Advantage really lies in opting for the run-time environment,since then it becomes much easier to move applications across from oneenvironment to another.andP;  AD/Advantage is immediately available for MVS, VSE,VM/CMS, CICS and IMS/DC environments with versions for VAX VMS and ICL's VMEsystems to follow next quarter.andP;  Thereafter versions will roll out for OS/2,MS-DOS, AIX, SCO Unix and Interactive Unix, to be followed next year byreleases for Bull, Siemens and Fujitsu operating environments.andP;  Pricingranges from #50,000 to #350,000 depending on CPU size.andO;</TEXT></DOC>